1
00:01:38,960 --> 00:01:41,785
[Episode 1]

2
00:01:50,319 --> 00:01:51,847
Uncle Sun.

3
00:01:52,720 --> 00:01:54,860
What exactly happened to my dad?

4
00:01:55,720 --> 00:01:57,679
Don't worry.

5
00:01:57,679 --> 00:02:00,520
Your dad was only taken in for questioning.

6
00:02:00,520 --> 00:02:02,279
Do I have to leave?

7
00:02:02,279 --> 00:02:04,759
The creditors have set their sights on you.

8
00:02:04,759 --> 00:02:07,360
I must take you to a safe place now.

9
00:02:07,360 --> 00:02:09,240
But I have my own plans.

10
00:02:09,240 --> 00:02:11,360
I've already got my foundation program offer.

11
00:02:11,360 --> 00:02:13,800
I want to follow my mom's last wishes
and study abroad.

12
00:02:13,800 --> 00:02:15,520
Ye,

13
00:02:15,520 --> 00:02:18,279
your father's assets have been frozen.

14
00:02:18,279 --> 00:02:20,119
It's hard to get a visa.

15
00:02:20,119 --> 00:02:22,800
Your family has no other relatives
here in Beijing.

16
00:02:22,800 --> 00:02:25,399
Right now,
I have to handle your father's affairs.

17
00:02:25,399 --> 00:02:27,240
Leaving you here...

18
00:02:27,240 --> 00:02:29,322
I just can't stop worrying.

19
00:02:32,879 --> 00:02:34,559
Then where are we going now?

20
00:02:34,559 --> 00:02:37,200
Zhazhating. To your aunt's place.

21
00:02:37,200 --> 00:02:39,447
Zhazhating?

22
00:02:44,985 --> 00:02:47,394
[Zhazhating]

23
00:03:00,159 --> 00:03:01,400
- Move way!
- Don't run!

24
00:03:01,400 --> 00:03:02,760
- Stop!
- Move!

25
00:03:02,760 --> 00:03:04,399
Move!

26
00:03:04,399 --> 00:03:06,697
Don't run! Stop!

27
00:03:07,679 --> 00:03:09,320
- Out of the way!
- Out of the way!

28
00:03:09,320 --> 00:03:11,520
Wu Lao Er! Wu Lao Er!

29
00:03:11,520 --> 00:03:12,520
Move, move, move!

30
00:03:12,520 --> 00:03:13,760
- Get out of the way!
- Move!

31
00:03:13,760 --> 00:03:15,430
Wu Lao Er!

32
00:03:16,320 --> 00:03:18,160
Wu! Wu!

33
00:03:18,160 --> 00:03:20,280
What's going on?

34
00:03:37,279 --> 00:03:39,279
C-C-Catch the thief!

35
00:03:39,279 --> 00:03:41,480
Wu Lao Er stole Mr. Zhu's phone!

36
00:03:41,480 --> 00:03:43,552
- What's wrong so early?
- Unbelievable!

37
00:03:43,552 --> 00:03:44,719
Mr. Zhu's phone was stolen.

38
00:03:44,719 --> 00:03:45,920
Mr. Zhu?

39
00:03:45,920 --> 00:03:47,999
- It was Wu Lao Er, wasn't it?
- Of course.

40
00:03:47,999 --> 00:03:50,439
Wu, don't forget to pick up your cousin!

41
00:03:50,439 --> 00:03:52,279
- Don't worry.
- Wu, follow me!

42
00:03:52,279 --> 00:03:53,640
- Slow down!
- Hurry, hurry!

43
00:03:53,640 --> 00:03:56,160
Be careful!

44
00:04:03,159 --> 00:04:04,719
Wu Lao Er!

45
00:04:04,719 --> 00:04:05,839
Isn't that Wu Lao Er?

46
00:04:05,839 --> 00:04:06,879
Stealing again?

47
00:04:06,879 --> 00:04:09,906
That kid has never done a good deed.

48
00:04:14,610 --> 00:04:15,679
Let's split up!

49
00:04:15,679 --> 00:04:17,710
- You got it!
- Okay.

50
00:04:28,080 --> 00:04:30,172
Wu Lao Er! Wu Lao Er!

51
00:04:32,359 --> 00:04:34,697
Hurry up, Fuzz!

52
00:04:52,080 --> 00:04:53,120
What's wrong?

53
00:04:53,120 --> 00:04:54,760
What's going on?

54
00:04:54,760 --> 00:04:57,460
The GPS isn't quite right.

55
00:05:27,799 --> 00:05:29,000
Oh my god.

56
00:05:29,000 --> 00:05:31,295
It's a swarm of punks.

57
00:05:31,919 --> 00:05:33,622
Run?

58
00:05:35,039 --> 00:05:36,372
Run?

59
00:05:37,080 --> 00:05:39,939
- Where's the phone?
- What phone?

60
00:05:40,640 --> 00:05:42,080
Don't play dumb with me.

61
00:05:42,080 --> 00:05:43,320
There are cameras on the street.

62
00:05:43,320 --> 00:05:45,239
You even dare to steal from a teacher, huh?

63
00:05:45,239 --> 00:05:47,765
No, what are you guys talking about?

64
00:05:49,310 --> 00:05:50,399
Wu! Wu!

65
00:05:50,399 --> 00:05:52,479
Look, I just swiped a phone.
No need to be so brutal!

66
00:05:52,479 --> 00:05:53,520
Hand it over.

67
00:05:53,520 --> 00:05:56,910
You're pinning me down. How can I hand it over?

68
00:06:09,581 --> 00:06:10,760
What are you doing?

69
00:06:10,760 --> 00:06:12,810
Getting the phone.

70
00:06:24,012 --> 00:06:25,581
Fuzz.

71
00:06:26,399 --> 00:06:27,960
Hu!

72
00:06:28,640 --> 00:06:30,960
- Take it.
- I...

73
00:06:44,039 --> 00:06:46,030
Get lost!

74
00:06:53,399 --> 00:06:54,640
A car from Beijing.

75
00:06:54,640 --> 00:06:55,760
Looks fancy.

76
00:06:55,760 --> 00:06:59,935
Wu. C-C-Could it be your cousin?

77
00:07:01,039 --> 00:07:02,479
Ye.

78
00:07:02,479 --> 00:07:03,560
I know.

79
00:07:03,560 --> 00:07:07,479
Things here might be a bit different
from what you expected.

80
00:07:07,479 --> 00:07:10,000
But at least you have
a relative to look after you.

81
00:07:10,000 --> 00:07:12,400
I've reminded them repeatedly.

82
00:07:12,400 --> 00:07:14,960
Make sure you stay safe.

83
00:07:14,960 --> 00:07:17,520
This is not a bit different.

84
00:07:17,520 --> 00:07:19,640
It's three people bullying one.

85
00:07:19,640 --> 00:07:21,872
The place is crawling with thugs.

86
00:07:23,479 --> 00:07:25,279
Ye.

87
00:07:25,279 --> 00:07:26,479
Don't get involved.

88
00:07:26,479 --> 00:07:29,635
Just get some fresh air. Who cares about them?

89
00:07:35,760 --> 00:07:38,440
What's this?

90
00:08:07,440 --> 00:08:10,200
Hey, beautiful.

91
00:08:10,200 --> 00:08:13,560
Hello. I am Hao Cheng Gong.

92
00:08:13,560 --> 00:08:15,320
The richest man in Zhazhating.

93
00:08:15,320 --> 00:08:17,422
What's wrong with you?

94
00:08:21,399 --> 00:08:22,760
You're from Beijing?

95
00:08:22,760 --> 00:08:24,839
None of your business.

96
00:08:25,880 --> 00:08:27,826
Hey, guys.

97
00:08:30,479 --> 00:08:32,040
You three.

98
00:08:32,040 --> 00:08:33,160
You're locals, right?

99
00:08:33,160 --> 00:08:34,680
Yeah, what of it?

100
00:08:34,680 --> 00:08:35,800
Just asking for directions.

101
00:08:35,800 --> 00:08:38,200
How do I get to Xuan Island?

102
00:08:38,200 --> 00:08:39,479
Xuan...?

103
00:08:39,479 --> 00:08:41,359
- Xuan Island.
- Go away...

104
00:08:41,359 --> 00:08:43,060
Not for free.

105
00:08:44,239 --> 00:08:46,621
- 100.
- 100?

106
00:08:46,621 --> 00:08:49,080
100 each, then.

107
00:08:51,479 --> 00:08:53,440
- Wait...
- Is that enough?

108
00:08:53,440 --> 00:08:54,719
No need to pay.

109
00:08:54,719 --> 00:08:57,080
The row of red houses across
from the lighthouse.

110
00:08:57,080 --> 00:08:58,960
Keep going along this road.

111
00:08:58,960 --> 00:09:00,320
Go about a kilometer on the main road.

112
00:09:00,320 --> 00:09:02,359
Turn left at the roundabout, then left again.

113
00:09:02,359 --> 00:09:04,639
Take the small path to the end.

114
00:09:04,639 --> 00:09:05,760
That's so complicated.

115
00:09:05,760 --> 00:09:09,320
No wonder the GPS got confused.
Take it, take it.

116
00:09:09,320 --> 00:09:10,359
Thank you.

117
00:09:10,359 --> 00:09:12,080
City people are so generous.

118
00:09:12,080 --> 00:09:13,480
Give it back.

119
00:09:13,480 --> 00:09:15,440
He's already in the car.
How can I give it back?

120
00:09:15,440 --> 00:09:18,410
He's like a walking ATM.

121
00:09:20,680 --> 00:09:22,400
Uncle Sun.

122
00:09:22,400 --> 00:09:23,863
Is this what you meant by...

123
00:09:23,863 --> 00:09:25,440
simple and honest locals?

124
00:09:25,440 --> 00:09:26,759
Small town.

125
00:09:26,759 --> 00:09:28,080
As long as the money is right,

126
00:09:28,080 --> 00:09:30,222
everything is easy.

127
00:10:05,119 --> 00:10:07,760
- Mr. Zhu.
- Mr. Zhu.

128
00:10:19,765 --> 00:10:21,960
Look at your hair. What are these colors?

129
00:10:21,960 --> 00:10:24,622
- Do you even look like students?
- Ow, ow, ow! That hurts!

130
00:10:25,197 --> 00:10:26,210
Where's Wu Lao Er?

131
00:10:26,210 --> 00:10:27,440
Don't worry. We found him.

132
00:10:27,440 --> 00:10:29,987
Wu gets things done.

133
00:10:30,880 --> 00:10:32,463
Here.

134
00:10:42,680 --> 00:10:43,839
See if there are any problems.

135
00:10:43,839 --> 00:10:46,759
- The phone is fine, but what's that smell?
- If it's fine,

136
00:10:46,759 --> 00:10:48,572
we should go.

137
00:10:49,639 --> 00:10:50,794
You two head back first.

138
00:10:50,794 --> 00:10:51,879
Xing Wu.

139
00:10:51,879 --> 00:10:54,382
Come with me. I need to talk to you.

140
00:10:56,839 --> 00:11:00,119
Take the shortcut and tell my mom
that my cousin is almost here.

141
00:11:00,119 --> 00:11:01,682
Okay.

142
00:11:01,682 --> 00:11:03,239
[Mahjong Club]

143
00:11:04,239 --> 00:11:07,359
Discard South first for peace of mind.

144
00:11:07,359 --> 00:11:09,800
Come back again. West Wind.

145
00:11:09,800 --> 00:11:11,119
Fang.

146
00:11:11,119 --> 00:11:13,800
Your makeup today is quite elaborate.

147
00:11:13,800 --> 00:11:15,647
Pretty nice, huh.

148
00:11:15,647 --> 00:11:18,122
What's the occasion?

149
00:11:18,122 --> 00:11:22,359
Isn't my niece from Beijing about to arrive?

150
00:11:22,359 --> 00:11:23,440
Fang Fang.

151
00:11:23,440 --> 00:11:25,600
I heard that your niece

152
00:11:25,600 --> 00:11:27,861
can get you 50,000 yuan.

153
00:11:28,599 --> 00:11:30,359
That's quite a lot.

154
00:11:31,359 --> 00:11:33,560
You're going to strike it rich.

155
00:11:33,560 --> 00:11:35,639
You can pay off all those debts.

156
00:11:35,639 --> 00:11:38,900
Who's the big mouth?

157
00:11:38,900 --> 00:11:40,120
Did you forget?

158
00:11:40,120 --> 00:11:42,960
Last time you were blowing my hair,
you told me yourself.

159
00:11:42,960 --> 00:11:45,085
You really have the memory of a fish.

160
00:11:45,719 --> 00:11:47,200
Right, right.

161
00:11:47,200 --> 00:11:48,880
I forgot.

162
00:11:48,880 --> 00:11:51,640
It's not about the money. She's family.

163
00:11:51,640 --> 00:11:53,920
Isn't it only natural to take care of her?

164
00:11:53,920 --> 00:11:55,160
I don't need the money.

165
00:11:55,160 --> 00:11:57,486
Fang Fang, you have relatives in the capital?

166
00:11:57,486 --> 00:11:58,840
Why didn't you ever mention it?

167
00:11:58,840 --> 00:12:01,080
Well, we haven't been in touch.

168
00:12:01,080 --> 00:12:04,560
She's my sister's child.
Her family's business is huge.

169
00:12:04,560 --> 00:12:05,719
So successful.

170
00:12:05,719 --> 00:12:07,839
But my sister passed away early.

171
00:12:07,839 --> 00:12:09,080
She passed away two years ago.

172
00:12:09,080 --> 00:12:12,639
My brother-in-law still treats me like family.

173
00:12:12,639 --> 00:12:14,839
I've already told my brother-in-law.

174
00:12:14,839 --> 00:12:17,920
He must come and develop our Zhazhating.

175
00:12:17,920 --> 00:12:21,541
He'll turn this place into a resort.
It's best to build an apartment block.

176
00:12:21,541 --> 00:12:23,935
I'll give each of you a unit then.

177
00:12:24,639 --> 00:12:26,525
- Really?
- Thank you!

178
00:12:26,525 --> 00:12:29,200
- I'll be waiting for that.
- Sure, sure.

179
00:12:29,200 --> 00:12:32,080
Your phone is ringing.

180
00:12:32,080 --> 00:12:33,719
Answer it first.

181
00:12:33,719 --> 00:12:35,752
Okay.

182
00:12:40,472 --> 00:12:42,280
Hey.

183
00:12:43,280 --> 00:12:44,359
Don't be in such a rush.

184
00:12:44,359 --> 00:12:45,800
Didn't I tell you?

185
00:12:45,800 --> 00:12:47,560
Once the money tree arrives,

186
00:12:47,560 --> 00:12:50,445
I'll wire you the money right away.

187
00:12:51,200 --> 00:12:53,372
Hello? Hello?

188
00:12:54,639 --> 00:12:57,122
What the hell?

189
00:13:01,640 --> 00:13:03,560
You're really persistent.

190
00:13:03,560 --> 00:13:05,119
You've been at it for two years.

191
00:13:05,119 --> 00:13:07,320
How many times has it been?

192
00:13:07,320 --> 00:13:10,960
We were teacher and student, after all.

193
00:13:10,960 --> 00:13:15,585
I just want to talk to you.
What about a heart-to-heart talk?

194
00:13:16,639 --> 00:13:18,359
I heard...

195
00:13:18,359 --> 00:13:21,960
you've been repairing phones at Shunyi
for almost two years now.

196
00:13:21,960 --> 00:13:24,119
What, are you addicted to repairs?

197
00:13:24,119 --> 00:13:27,400
Do you really not plan to return
and take the college entrance exam?

198
00:13:27,400 --> 00:13:29,160
How do you know...

199
00:13:29,160 --> 00:13:31,810
I'll get into a good college if I return?

200
00:13:32,800 --> 00:13:34,440
I think I'm doing fine now.

201
00:13:34,440 --> 00:13:37,560
I'm your teacher. Don't I know you?

202
00:13:37,560 --> 00:13:39,560
You just feel that...

203
00:13:39,560 --> 00:13:41,400
your mom is all alone now.

204
00:13:41,400 --> 00:13:42,719
She has to pay for your school,

205
00:13:42,719 --> 00:13:44,239
pay off the family debts,

206
00:13:44,239 --> 00:13:46,280
and find time to take care of your grandma.

207
00:13:46,280 --> 00:13:49,489
So you want to help her out.

208
00:13:50,839 --> 00:13:53,119
But Xing Wu, can't you use your brain?

209
00:13:53,119 --> 00:13:55,800
Come back to school now.

210
00:13:55,800 --> 00:13:57,760
Prepare to get into a good college.

211
00:13:57,760 --> 00:14:01,047
That's the best way to repay your mom.

212
00:14:01,759 --> 00:14:02,999
Look.

213
00:14:02,999 --> 00:14:05,999
You used to be quite a big deal around here.

214
00:14:05,999 --> 00:14:08,519
Remember that paper airplane
contest in Zhazhating?

215
00:14:08,519 --> 00:14:11,937
- The airplane you made flew so high and--
- All right, all right.

216
00:14:11,937 --> 00:14:13,560
It was just a stupid paper airplane.

217
00:14:13,560 --> 00:14:14,759
Can you stop bringing it up?

218
00:14:14,759 --> 00:14:17,400
And that aerospace model contest then,
weren't you the champion too?

219
00:14:17,400 --> 00:14:18,920
Wu Lao Er was your student too.

220
00:14:18,920 --> 00:14:20,280
He's been stealing for two years
since he graduated--

221
00:14:20,280 --> 00:14:24,359
Don't mention him to me, okay?
He's different from you.

222
00:14:24,359 --> 00:14:27,720
There's a gap between people.

223
00:14:27,720 --> 00:14:30,360
Just like our Zhazhating.

224
00:14:30,360 --> 00:14:32,640
Different alleys, different accents.

225
00:14:32,640 --> 00:14:34,879
Different paths, different folks.

226
00:14:34,879 --> 00:14:37,080
Anyway, in my eyes,

227
00:14:37,080 --> 00:14:39,239
you're a promising talent.

228
00:14:39,239 --> 00:14:41,400
When your mom withdrew you,

229
00:14:41,400 --> 00:14:43,639
she had no other choice.

230
00:14:43,639 --> 00:14:45,639
Some things are in the past.

231
00:14:45,639 --> 00:14:49,160
It's been two years, what's holding you back?

232
00:14:53,775 --> 00:14:55,761
Are you and your wife still fighting?

233
00:14:55,761 --> 00:14:58,080
He Xiao Lian and I...

234
00:14:58,080 --> 00:15:01,080
We're talking about you.
Why bring me into this?

235
00:15:01,080 --> 00:15:03,639
Xing Wu.
I've talked to you so many times this year.

236
00:15:03,639 --> 00:15:06,250
Listen up, think about it.

237
00:15:06,999 --> 00:15:08,359
Are you done?

238
00:15:08,359 --> 00:15:09,759
I'm done listening.

239
00:15:09,759 --> 00:15:11,685
Goodbye, Mr. Zhu.

240
00:15:13,200 --> 00:15:15,040
Think it over!

241
00:15:15,040 --> 00:15:17,760
Call me when you've decided.

242
00:15:18,960 --> 00:15:20,119
Auntie Fang!

243
00:15:20,119 --> 00:15:21,479
C-C-Cousin...

244
00:15:21,479 --> 00:15:22,960
Auntie Fang!

245
00:15:22,960 --> 00:15:25,599
Your niece is here.
Xing Wu told me to let you know.

246
00:15:25,599 --> 00:15:26,639
Son!

247
00:15:26,639 --> 00:15:28,800
What's with your hair? Who dyed it for you?

248
00:15:28,800 --> 00:15:30,160
Me! I did.

249
00:15:30,160 --> 00:15:32,160
I just got that new hair dye cream.

250
00:15:32,160 --> 00:15:35,040
They're not in school right now,
so I'm using them as test subjects.

251
00:15:35,040 --> 00:15:36,566
But it looks terrible.

252
00:15:36,566 --> 00:15:38,720
They'll look like traffic lights
standing there.

253
00:15:38,720 --> 00:15:41,440
- Dye it back for them.
- Dye it back right now.

254
00:15:41,440 --> 00:15:42,519
- Fine.
- Looking like some punk.

255
00:15:42,519 --> 00:15:43,759
Fine, fine.

256
00:15:43,759 --> 00:15:45,200
Fuzz, Hu.

257
00:15:45,200 --> 00:15:46,200
Tell Liu Nian.

258
00:15:46,200 --> 00:15:47,719
Set off the firecrackers!

259
00:15:47,719 --> 00:15:48,719
- Okay.
- Got it.

260
00:15:48,719 --> 00:15:51,080
Gosh, look at this hair color.

261
00:15:51,080 --> 00:15:52,200
Hold my bag for a second.

262
00:15:52,200 --> 00:15:54,600
I'm going to welcome my money tree.

263
00:15:54,600 --> 00:15:56,800
- We're all going.
- Let's go, let's go.

264
00:15:56,800 --> 00:15:58,910
- I'll take it.
- Okay.

265
00:15:58,910 --> 00:16:04,722
[Zhazhating]

266
00:16:06,160 --> 00:16:07,959
She's here, she's here.

267
00:16:16,839 --> 00:16:18,040
Is she here?

268
00:16:18,040 --> 00:16:20,330
Light it up! Light it!

269
00:16:50,160 --> 00:16:51,239
Oh, my.

270
00:16:51,239 --> 00:16:53,434
- How lively!
- Welcome, welcome!

271
00:16:57,359 --> 00:16:59,320
Hello. You're Qing Ye's aunt?

272
00:16:59,320 --> 00:17:00,599
- Yes, that's right.
- Li Lan Fang?

273
00:17:00,599 --> 00:17:03,066
- Yes, yes.
- We spoke on the phone.

274
00:17:03,066 --> 00:17:04,759
- Secretary Sun Hai.
- Yes, exactly.

275
00:17:04,759 --> 00:17:06,319
Hello, hello.

276
00:17:06,319 --> 00:17:08,656
- That's Ye.
- Yes.

277
00:17:27,400 --> 00:17:31,403
Ye, I finally get to see you. Give me a hug.

278
00:17:32,039 --> 00:17:34,120
So stylish.

279
00:17:34,120 --> 00:17:37,120
She's really from the city.

280
00:17:37,120 --> 00:17:38,880
You've grown so tall.

281
00:17:38,880 --> 00:17:39,880
Do you remember me?

282
00:17:39,880 --> 00:17:42,360
You came here when you were little.

283
00:17:43,519 --> 00:17:44,719
It's okay if you don't remember.

284
00:17:44,719 --> 00:17:45,999
You're here now, anyway.

285
00:17:45,999 --> 00:17:49,319
Don't you worry. From now on, I, your aunt,

286
00:17:49,319 --> 00:17:52,135
will take good care of you.

287
00:17:53,440 --> 00:17:54,559
Listen up, neighbors!

288
00:17:54,559 --> 00:17:57,759
This is my niece who came all the way
from Beijing.

289
00:17:57,759 --> 00:17:59,519
Qing Ye.

290
00:17:59,519 --> 00:18:00,519
Good.

291
00:18:00,519 --> 00:18:01,840
Welcome, welcome!

292
00:18:01,840 --> 00:18:04,400
Hope you all look out for her.

293
00:18:04,400 --> 00:18:06,210
Sure, no problem.

294
00:18:06,840 --> 00:18:07,880
Thank you.

295
00:18:07,880 --> 00:18:10,640
Liu Nian, go get the suitcases.

296
00:18:11,360 --> 00:18:13,200
That's all, everyone. Thank you.

297
00:18:13,200 --> 00:18:14,719
- We can head off now.
- Wonderful.

298
00:18:14,719 --> 00:18:16,972
Let's go, let's go.

299
00:18:16,972 --> 00:18:18,947
Come on, let's go inside.

300
00:18:18,947 --> 00:18:21,039
I want to say a few words to Uncle Sun.

301
00:18:21,039 --> 00:18:23,200
Sure, no problem. We'll head in first.

302
00:18:23,200 --> 00:18:24,440
Liu Nian, hurry up.

303
00:18:24,440 --> 00:18:26,475
Coming!

304
00:18:29,519 --> 00:18:30,960
Uncle Sun.

305
00:18:30,960 --> 00:18:32,799
You've been with my dad for so many years.

306
00:18:32,799 --> 00:18:34,799
You must prove his innocence.

307
00:18:34,799 --> 00:18:36,400
Even if it costs me my life,

308
00:18:36,400 --> 00:18:37,999
I will do my absolute best.

309
00:18:37,999 --> 00:18:39,120
Don't worry.

310
00:18:39,120 --> 00:18:40,600
Ye.

311
00:18:40,600 --> 00:18:42,440
Take good care of yourself here.

312
00:18:42,440 --> 00:18:43,640
If anything happens,

313
00:18:43,640 --> 00:18:45,160
call me anytime.

314
00:18:45,160 --> 00:18:46,869
I'm off.

315
00:18:53,735 --> 00:18:56,035
[Xuan Island Barbershop]

316
00:19:09,680 --> 00:19:11,162
Ye.

317
00:19:11,759 --> 00:19:13,120
This is Xuan Island.

318
00:19:13,120 --> 00:19:16,497
Welcome to Xuan Island. This is my little shop.

319
00:19:16,497 --> 00:19:18,479
It might look a bit messy,

320
00:19:18,479 --> 00:19:20,440
but there's

321
00:19:20,440 --> 00:19:23,148
order in the chaos.

322
00:19:23,148 --> 00:19:24,440
This is Liu Nian, my apprentice.

323
00:19:24,440 --> 00:19:25,559
Hello.

324
00:19:25,559 --> 00:19:27,299
Go sweep up the firecrackers outside.

325
00:19:27,299 --> 00:19:28,519
Don't let the neighbors complain.

326
00:19:28,519 --> 00:19:30,456
Okay.

327
00:19:42,840 --> 00:19:44,522
Thank you.

328
00:19:49,759 --> 00:19:51,385
30,000?

329
00:19:52,120 --> 00:19:54,897
Didn't we agree on 50,000?

330
00:19:54,897 --> 00:19:56,759
This is what I've decided.

331
00:19:56,759 --> 00:19:59,079
Our place here,

332
00:19:59,079 --> 00:20:00,319
though it's small,

333
00:20:00,319 --> 00:20:04,097
it has everything you need.

334
00:20:04,097 --> 00:20:05,719
We had a deal.

335
00:20:05,719 --> 00:20:07,840
50,000 for room and board.

336
00:20:07,840 --> 00:20:09,400
Did you get the amount wrong?

337
00:20:09,400 --> 00:20:12,239
I won't be staying here for long.

338
00:20:12,239 --> 00:20:13,960
This money...

339
00:20:13,960 --> 00:20:15,239
Compared to a hotel,

340
00:20:15,239 --> 00:20:16,360
it's more than enough.

341
00:20:16,360 --> 00:20:17,680
The remaining 20,000

342
00:20:17,680 --> 00:20:19,319
will be the final payment.

343
00:20:19,319 --> 00:20:20,920
I'll give it to you when I leave.

344
00:20:20,920 --> 00:20:22,885
Okay.

345
00:20:22,885 --> 00:20:24,600
We're all family here.

346
00:20:24,600 --> 00:20:27,079
Just make yourself at home, okay?

347
00:20:27,079 --> 00:20:32,160
I promise, staying here will feel like home.

348
00:20:32,160 --> 00:20:33,319
This is my son,

349
00:20:33,319 --> 00:20:35,072
Xing Wu.

350
00:20:38,480 --> 00:20:40,120
This is your cousin from Beijing,

351
00:20:40,120 --> 00:20:42,144
Qing Ye.

352
00:20:51,960 --> 00:20:54,200
I have to go next door in a bit.

353
00:20:54,200 --> 00:20:58,597
So, um... Take Qing Ye to show her around.

354
00:20:59,640 --> 00:21:02,092
I'm busy. No time.

355
00:21:13,239 --> 00:21:15,719
It's fine. I'll take you upstairs.

356
00:21:15,719 --> 00:21:17,547
Let's see the room.

357
00:21:47,720 --> 00:21:49,139
Seriously,

358
00:21:49,139 --> 00:21:52,020
what on earth do you have in here?

359
00:21:52,020 --> 00:21:55,010
This is way too heavy.

360
00:21:56,719 --> 00:21:58,239
Come on.

361
00:21:58,239 --> 00:21:59,822
Here.

362
00:22:03,840 --> 00:22:08,822
This is where my son repairs phones and things.

363
00:22:11,120 --> 00:22:12,400
Come in.

364
00:22:12,400 --> 00:22:14,322
You'll sleep here.

365
00:22:17,799 --> 00:22:19,559
I'm sleeping here?

366
00:22:19,559 --> 00:22:21,239
Isn't this your son's room?

367
00:22:21,239 --> 00:22:22,360
That's right.

368
00:22:22,360 --> 00:22:24,520
He doesn't come back much. Always out there.

369
00:22:24,520 --> 00:22:26,200
Look how nice it is to sleep here.

370
00:22:26,200 --> 00:22:28,640
Facing the sea, with spring blossoms.

371
00:22:28,640 --> 00:22:30,440
You sleep here,

372
00:22:30,440 --> 00:22:31,440
and he sleeps there.

373
00:22:31,440 --> 00:22:33,719
If you find it inconvenient,

374
00:22:33,719 --> 00:22:35,559
there's a curtain in the middle.

375
00:22:35,559 --> 00:22:37,799
And if you still find it inconvenient,

376
00:22:37,799 --> 00:22:39,640
I'll replace it with a board.

377
00:22:39,640 --> 00:22:40,759
How about that?

378
00:22:40,759 --> 00:22:43,156
Are there any other options?

379
00:22:49,479 --> 00:22:52,097
Come, take a look.

380
00:22:52,097 --> 00:22:54,319
This is my room.

381
00:22:54,319 --> 00:22:55,640
It may look small,

382
00:22:55,640 --> 00:22:58,079
It's small but well-arranged.

383
00:22:58,079 --> 00:23:00,110
Cluttered but orderly.

384
00:23:00,759 --> 00:23:01,960
Take a look.

385
00:23:01,960 --> 00:23:03,360
You can stay here.

386
00:23:03,360 --> 00:23:05,760
It'll be ready once it's tidied up.

387
00:23:07,239 --> 00:23:09,697
So, which room?

388
00:23:11,947 --> 00:23:13,440
Oh my god, this...

389
00:23:13,440 --> 00:23:16,239
Don't be scared. It's okay.

390
00:23:16,239 --> 00:23:19,640
This? Liu Nian uses this for hair rollers.

391
00:23:19,640 --> 00:23:20,840
Have you decided?

392
00:23:20,840 --> 00:23:22,960
Fang, we're waiting for you!

393
00:23:22,960 --> 00:23:24,160
Hurry up!

394
00:23:24,160 --> 00:23:25,759
Coming!

395
00:23:25,759 --> 00:23:28,319
How about this? Take your time.

396
00:23:28,319 --> 00:23:30,600
I'm going to play a few rounds.

397
00:23:30,600 --> 00:23:33,200
I'll have Xing Wu show you around later.

398
00:23:33,200 --> 00:23:36,247
Just go to him if you need anything.

399
00:23:36,247 --> 00:23:39,210
There, there, don't be scared.

400
00:23:53,479 --> 00:23:54,880
What are you doing?

401
00:23:54,880 --> 00:23:56,239
Who upset you?

402
00:23:56,239 --> 00:23:57,880
Why are you so cold to your cousin?

403
00:23:57,880 --> 00:23:59,600
You two used to play together
when you were little.

404
00:23:59,600 --> 00:24:01,600
You went beachcombing. Forgot?

405
00:24:01,600 --> 00:24:03,880
The poor girl has had it rough.

406
00:24:03,880 --> 00:24:05,999
Her mother passed away years ago.

407
00:24:05,999 --> 00:24:10,519
I bet if it weren't for the trouble at home,
her dad would never have sent her here.

408
00:24:10,519 --> 00:24:11,920
We haven't been in touch for years,

409
00:24:11,920 --> 00:24:13,747
and she only comes when in trouble.

410
00:24:14,360 --> 00:24:15,680
My sister was so good to me.

411
00:24:15,680 --> 00:24:17,880
I was sent to live with them when I was eight.

412
00:24:17,880 --> 00:24:20,840
She treated me just like her own sister.

413
00:24:20,840 --> 00:24:22,559
Besides, after I was pregnant with you,

414
00:24:22,559 --> 00:24:25,785
she secretly gave me a lot of money.

415
00:24:26,799 --> 00:24:28,999
Service with a smile, okay?

416
00:24:28,999 --> 00:24:31,148
She's an honored guest.

417
00:24:32,039 --> 00:24:33,640
Ye,

418
00:24:33,640 --> 00:24:35,200
if Xing Wu isn't around,

419
00:24:35,200 --> 00:24:38,310
you can ask Liu Nian for help.

420
00:24:38,920 --> 00:24:40,374
Wu.

421
00:24:40,374 --> 00:24:41,947
Okay.

422
00:24:45,385 --> 00:24:46,835
Hey.

423
00:24:46,835 --> 00:24:49,319
Where's the bathroom?

424
00:24:49,319 --> 00:24:50,317
Outside.

425
00:24:50,317 --> 00:24:51,840
It's shared.

426
00:24:51,840 --> 00:24:53,000
Shared?

427
00:24:53,000 --> 00:24:55,160
Is there a problem?

428
00:24:56,640 --> 00:24:57,799
Also...

429
00:24:57,799 --> 00:24:58,880
This is my grandma's room.

430
00:24:58,880 --> 00:24:59,880
She's resting.

431
00:24:59,880 --> 00:25:01,319
Don't go in unless you have to.

432
00:25:01,319 --> 00:25:03,160
Don't touch anything on the first floor.

433
00:25:03,160 --> 00:25:05,120
This is my number.

434
00:25:05,120 --> 00:25:07,033
I have things to do.

435
00:25:10,079 --> 00:25:12,535
Call me if anything.

436
00:26:16,120 --> 00:26:18,560
[Temporary Residency Service Contract]

437
00:27:18,840 --> 00:27:20,497
Mom.

438
00:27:21,719 --> 00:27:24,120
Sweetie, you're awake.

439
00:27:24,120 --> 00:27:25,239
Mom.

440
00:27:25,239 --> 00:27:27,319
I just had a nightmare.

441
00:27:27,319 --> 00:27:29,347
It scared me.

442
00:27:30,160 --> 00:27:31,640
Silly child.

443
00:27:31,640 --> 00:27:33,200
It was just a dream.

444
00:27:33,200 --> 00:27:36,185
What did you dream about?
Tell me about it.

445
00:27:36,840 --> 00:27:38,600
I dreamed of a place

446
00:27:38,600 --> 00:27:41,039
called Zhazhating.

447
00:27:41,039 --> 00:27:42,680
I met my aunt,

448
00:27:42,680 --> 00:27:44,559
Li Lan Fang,

449
00:27:44,559 --> 00:27:47,039
and her son, Xing Wu.

450
00:27:47,039 --> 00:27:48,400
And also...

451
00:27:48,400 --> 00:27:50,960
his friends.

452
00:27:50,960 --> 00:27:52,680
They were so weird.

453
00:27:52,680 --> 00:27:55,120
Their hair was all colors,
and they had bad attitudes.

454
00:27:55,120 --> 00:27:57,310
I didn't like it at all.

455
00:27:57,880 --> 00:27:59,120
Don't be afraid.

456
00:27:59,120 --> 00:28:01,810
It was only a dream.

457
00:28:16,440 --> 00:28:17,935
Mom.

458
00:28:18,920 --> 00:28:19,999
Mom.

459
00:28:19,999 --> 00:28:20,999
Mom.

460
00:28:20,999 --> 00:28:22,660
Mom.

461
00:28:31,039 --> 00:28:32,319
What are you doing here?

462
00:28:32,319 --> 00:28:34,160
Having a nightmare?

463
00:28:35,440 --> 00:28:37,197
No, I'm not.

464
00:28:38,680 --> 00:28:40,360
Good.

465
00:28:42,999 --> 00:28:44,797
Do you need something?

466
00:28:45,719 --> 00:28:47,400
My honored guest,

467
00:28:47,400 --> 00:28:50,072
my mom's calling you downstairs for dinner.

468
00:28:51,160 --> 00:28:53,010
I got it.

469
00:29:05,600 --> 00:29:08,520
Ye, come and eat.

470
00:29:10,239 --> 00:29:11,840
Auntie,

471
00:29:11,840 --> 00:29:15,319
is the light here always this dim?

472
00:29:15,319 --> 00:29:17,239
Yes.

473
00:29:17,239 --> 00:29:18,920
Did you ask Grandma?

474
00:29:18,920 --> 00:29:21,880
Is she coming out to eat,
or should we bring it to her?

475
00:29:21,880 --> 00:29:24,210
Grandma said she's not hungry yet.

476
00:29:26,147 --> 00:29:28,710
Xing Wu's grandma has bad legs.

477
00:29:28,710 --> 00:29:30,120
Well, today,

478
00:29:30,120 --> 00:29:31,680
to welcome Ye,

479
00:29:31,680 --> 00:29:33,440
I specially made three dishes.

480
00:29:33,440 --> 00:29:34,680
The soup is in the pot.

481
00:29:34,680 --> 00:29:36,640
It'll be ready in a bit.

482
00:29:36,640 --> 00:29:37,759
Here, Ye.

483
00:29:37,759 --> 00:29:40,920
Have a piece of meat.

484
00:29:41,920 --> 00:29:43,120
Thank you.

485
00:29:43,120 --> 00:29:45,200
I don't eat meat at night.

486
00:29:46,200 --> 00:29:47,759
You don't eat meat?

487
00:29:47,759 --> 00:29:50,560
You're still growing. How can you not eat meat?

488
00:29:50,560 --> 00:29:54,120
Consuming too much fat is bad for health.

489
00:29:54,920 --> 00:29:56,600
Then have some seafood.

490
00:29:56,600 --> 00:29:57,600
Clams won't make you fat.

491
00:29:57,600 --> 00:29:59,559
Eat up.

492
00:29:59,559 --> 00:30:01,319
As the saying goes,

493
00:30:01,319 --> 00:30:03,799
"Oysters in cold water, clams in hot water."

494
00:30:03,799 --> 00:30:05,720
With a spoonful of lard,

495
00:30:05,720 --> 00:30:08,090
it's incredibly delicious.

496
00:30:08,090 --> 00:30:10,280
Stir-frying with lard is delicious!

497
00:30:10,280 --> 00:30:12,560
I don't eat lard.

498
00:30:14,319 --> 00:30:15,760
Don't eat it if you don't want to.

499
00:30:15,760 --> 00:30:17,079
Wu.

500
00:30:17,079 --> 00:30:18,920
Go across the street later.

501
00:30:18,920 --> 00:30:20,239
Get Ye a bowl of noodles.

502
00:30:20,239 --> 00:30:21,640
No need.

503
00:30:21,640 --> 00:30:23,597
I'm not hungry.

504
00:30:24,999 --> 00:30:28,430
I came down just to show you this.

505
00:30:32,952 --> 00:30:35,640
Temporary Residency Service Contract.

506
00:30:35,640 --> 00:30:37,719
If you are rich, stay in a hotel.

507
00:30:37,719 --> 00:30:39,680
This childish contract is invalid with me.

508
00:30:39,680 --> 00:30:41,319
What's wrong with a contract?

509
00:30:41,319 --> 00:30:42,960
Ye has already paid.

510
00:30:42,960 --> 00:30:44,799
What's the big deal about signing a contract?

511
00:30:44,799 --> 00:30:45,920
I'll sign it.

512
00:30:45,920 --> 00:30:49,060
You city people
are particular about everything.

513
00:30:49,719 --> 00:30:52,497
There's one more thing I want to say.

514
00:30:52,497 --> 00:30:54,039
During my stay here,

515
00:30:54,039 --> 00:30:57,999
if my personal safety is compromised
or something,

516
00:30:57,999 --> 00:31:00,624
I won't pay the remaining balance.

517
00:31:00,624 --> 00:31:02,572
Don't worry.

518
00:31:02,572 --> 00:31:05,621
Nothing like that will ever happen.

519
00:31:06,319 --> 00:31:08,360
It better be.

520
00:31:10,479 --> 00:31:12,479
Fine. There are two copies of the contract.

521
00:31:12,479 --> 00:31:13,559
You keep this one.

522
00:31:13,559 --> 00:31:15,297
Okay.

523
00:31:16,680 --> 00:31:18,635
I'm going upstairs.

524
00:31:20,400 --> 00:31:22,720
Are you sure you don't eat something?

525
00:31:22,720 --> 00:31:24,735
I'm not hungry.

526
00:31:31,400 --> 00:31:33,160
Is life not hard enough as it is?

527
00:31:33,160 --> 00:31:34,920
Why bring home a princess to serve?

528
00:31:34,920 --> 00:31:38,597
Before you show mercy to others,
can't you get your own life in order first?

529
00:31:39,440 --> 00:31:42,766
Whose fault is it that our lives are like this?

530
00:31:42,766 --> 00:31:45,920
All because of that unreliable Xing Guo Dong.

531
00:31:45,920 --> 00:31:48,480
If he hadn't gambled everything away
and mortgaged Xuan Island,

532
00:31:48,480 --> 00:31:49,720
would I have to scrape together money

533
00:31:49,720 --> 00:31:52,880
for your tuition and
your grandma's medical bills?

534
00:31:52,880 --> 00:31:56,120
Do you think the little you make
from repairs can fill this massive hole?

535
00:31:56,120 --> 00:31:58,840
- Enough already.
- What's enough? I'm not done yet.

536
00:31:58,840 --> 00:32:00,440
Your grandma can't walk well now,

537
00:32:00,440 --> 00:32:01,719
and she has epilepsy.

538
00:32:01,719 --> 00:32:03,999
Every hospital visit costs money.

539
00:32:03,999 --> 00:32:07,479
Let me tell you,
if it weren't for Qing Ye's 30,000 today,

540
00:32:07,479 --> 00:32:12,280
You, me, your grandma,
none of us escapes those debt collectors.

541
00:32:12,280 --> 00:32:14,760
So, she is our savior now.

542
00:32:14,760 --> 00:32:17,000
We have to treat her well!

543
00:32:24,400 --> 00:32:26,097
I know.

544
00:32:26,880 --> 00:32:30,079
It hasn't been easy for you to support us.

545
00:32:30,079 --> 00:32:32,160
As your mother,

546
00:32:32,160 --> 00:32:35,253
my heart aches for you,
and I don't want you to be so exhausted.

547
00:32:35,920 --> 00:32:37,799
Let's pay off the debt first,

548
00:32:37,799 --> 00:32:39,960
and then work hard.

549
00:32:39,960 --> 00:32:43,120
Maybe then you can go back to school.

550
00:32:43,759 --> 00:32:45,799
I believe that with your talent,

551
00:32:45,799 --> 00:32:48,239
you can definitely get into a good college.

552
00:32:48,239 --> 00:32:51,247
Education is the only way out.

553
00:32:51,920 --> 00:32:54,412
Who said I'm going to college?

554
00:32:55,413 --> 00:32:57,785
I can support us.

555
00:33:00,039 --> 00:33:02,680
Can we just treat this money as a loan?

556
00:33:02,680 --> 00:33:05,040
We'll pay her back
when we have the money, okay?

557
00:33:05,040 --> 00:33:07,160
You know, to our family, she's like

558
00:33:07,160 --> 00:33:10,560
'A terrible hand,
but pulled a winning tile after a kong'.

559
00:33:10,560 --> 00:33:14,240
Li Lan Fang,
why must you relate everything to mahjong?

560
00:33:14,240 --> 00:33:19,160
Well, son.
Look, everyone needs a pillar of support.

561
00:33:19,160 --> 00:33:21,400
You can't overanalyze everything.

562
00:33:21,400 --> 00:33:22,802
Take me, for example.

563
00:33:22,802 --> 00:33:23,840
In this life,

564
00:33:23,840 --> 00:33:25,960
I'm here to pay back Xing Guo Dong's debt.

565
00:33:25,960 --> 00:33:27,840
And you,

566
00:33:27,840 --> 00:33:30,160
you're here to pay back mine.

567
00:33:31,999 --> 00:33:35,860
I went through a lot of pain
to bring you into this world.

568
00:33:37,920 --> 00:33:41,037
Actually, I'm not that hungry.

569
00:33:43,006 --> 00:33:44,400
Playing mahjong again?

570
00:33:44,400 --> 00:33:45,999
Just let me go.

571
00:33:45,999 --> 00:33:47,319
Okay?

572
00:33:47,319 --> 00:33:49,120
Go, go, go.

573
00:33:49,120 --> 00:33:52,572
All right! Clean up these things, okay?

574
00:34:12,360 --> 00:34:13,960
Wu.

575
00:34:13,960 --> 00:34:16,183
Wu.

576
00:34:19,960 --> 00:34:21,440
- Grandma.
- Come in.

577
00:34:21,440 --> 00:34:22,840
Here.

578
00:34:23,920 --> 00:34:26,800
I know it's not easy for you and your mom.

579
00:34:26,800 --> 00:34:28,679
Don't be angry with her.

580
00:34:28,679 --> 00:34:30,240
Just let her go.

581
00:34:30,240 --> 00:34:33,747
When she's playing mahjong,
she's actually a bit happier.

582
00:34:36,679 --> 00:34:38,559
I know, Grandma.

583
00:34:38,559 --> 00:34:41,235
I'll go get you some food.

584
00:34:41,235 --> 00:34:42,559
I'm not hungry.

585
00:34:42,559 --> 00:34:45,785
Eating too much at night is bad for digestion.

586
00:34:46,920 --> 00:34:49,079
Don't you love steamed eggs with sea urchin?

587
00:34:49,079 --> 00:34:50,360
Once I get paid for this job,

588
00:34:50,360 --> 00:34:52,135
I'll buy some for you.

589
00:34:53,079 --> 00:34:56,247
My grandson is so filial.

590
00:35:02,199 --> 00:35:03,735
What happened?

591
00:35:03,735 --> 00:35:05,740
Must be a power outage.

592
00:35:06,400 --> 00:35:08,622
I'll go check, Grandma.

593
00:35:17,639 --> 00:35:19,642
I left in such a hurry this time.

594
00:35:19,642 --> 00:35:21,440
I didn't bring anything.

595
00:35:21,440 --> 00:35:24,039
I even left my laptop at school.

596
00:35:24,039 --> 00:35:26,235
Okay, I'll mail it to you tomorrow.

597
00:35:27,039 --> 00:35:29,199
Send it express.
I need it to register for classes.

598
00:35:29,199 --> 00:35:31,822
Okay, don't worry. I got it.

599
00:35:31,822 --> 00:35:35,440
Qing Ye, how long do you plan to stay there?

600
00:35:35,440 --> 00:35:36,840
Let me see...

601
00:35:36,840 --> 00:35:38,000
Look...

602
00:35:38,000 --> 00:35:40,280
Registering for classes,
waiting for the visa...

603
00:35:40,280 --> 00:35:41,566
By the way, Le Ling,

604
00:35:41,566 --> 00:35:44,721
did you get my proof of assets ready?

605
00:35:44,721 --> 00:35:45,761
Almost.

606
00:35:45,761 --> 00:35:47,039
I'm asking my mom to move some funds.

607
00:35:47,039 --> 00:35:48,400
It should be ready by next week.

608
00:35:48,400 --> 00:35:49,880
That's great.

609
00:35:49,880 --> 00:35:51,840
Then I guess I'll only be here a month.

610
00:35:51,840 --> 00:35:55,239
A month. Then I can finally leave this dump.

611
00:35:55,239 --> 00:35:56,822
Let me show you guys.

612
00:35:57,559 --> 00:36:00,585
Qing Ye, why haven't you turned on the lights?

613
00:36:01,360 --> 00:36:02,440
Can you believe it?

614
00:36:02,440 --> 00:36:03,559
There's a power outage here.

615
00:36:03,559 --> 00:36:04,559
A power outage?

616
00:36:04,559 --> 00:36:06,119
How can there be a power outage?

617
00:36:06,119 --> 00:36:09,519
Qing Ye, did you really go on X-Change?

618
00:36:09,519 --> 00:36:11,360
I'm telling you, it's unbelievable.

619
00:36:11,360 --> 00:36:13,079
It's so bizarre.

620
00:36:13,079 --> 00:36:14,840
Forget it.

621
00:36:14,840 --> 00:36:16,329
Not in the mood.

622
00:36:16,329 --> 00:36:18,000
Hey, don't you have a cousin there?

623
00:36:18,000 --> 00:36:19,597
How is he?

624
00:36:19,597 --> 00:36:21,079
Him?

625
00:36:21,079 --> 00:36:24,679
It's a long story.
His hair's so weird, not golden, not silver.

626
00:36:24,679 --> 00:36:25,960
And he has a foul temper.

627
00:36:25,960 --> 00:36:28,840
He's exactly like some punk you'd imagine.

628
00:36:28,840 --> 00:36:30,400
Just like a little thug.

629
00:36:30,400 --> 00:36:31,519
Qing Ye!

630
00:36:31,519 --> 00:36:33,909
There's a ghost behind you!

631
00:36:36,541 --> 00:36:38,352
Ugh. You walk without making a sound?

632
00:36:38,352 --> 00:36:42,280
So I can hear you talking behind my back.

633
00:36:42,280 --> 00:36:44,497
Talk to you guys later.

634
00:36:51,440 --> 00:36:53,210
Stay in the dark then.

635
00:37:06,635 --> 00:37:07,997
[Xuan Island Barbershop]

636
00:37:24,559 --> 00:37:28,022
What's that smell? So pungent.

637
00:37:29,480 --> 00:37:30,800
Haven't you ever used a mosquito coil?

638
00:37:30,800 --> 00:37:32,400
Don't you have electric ones here?

639
00:37:32,400 --> 00:37:33,840
The odorless, non-toxic kind.

640
00:37:33,840 --> 00:37:35,639
We have plenty of sea mosquitoes here.

641
00:37:35,639 --> 00:37:38,360
This kind of coil works best.

642
00:37:41,079 --> 00:37:42,747
By the way,

643
00:37:43,519 --> 00:37:45,360
a friendly tip.

644
00:37:45,360 --> 00:37:47,960
These mosquitoes can bite a pig to death.

645
00:37:47,960 --> 00:37:49,119
How many times have you been bitten?

646
00:37:49,119 --> 00:37:50,835
Who are you calling a pig?

647
00:37:51,480 --> 00:37:53,840
It seems my summary of you
wasn't thorough enough.

648
00:37:53,840 --> 00:37:57,182
Add two more. Sarcastic! Mysterious!

649
00:37:57,182 --> 00:37:58,440
And one more thing.

650
00:37:58,440 --> 00:37:59,840
Don't talk to me much.

651
00:37:59,840 --> 00:38:01,710
I'm a germaphobe.

652
00:38:14,039 --> 00:38:15,119
What now?

653
00:38:15,119 --> 00:38:17,147
Another blackout.

654
00:38:18,719 --> 00:38:19,960
What are you doing?

655
00:38:19,960 --> 00:38:21,440
Didn't you say it was too dark?

656
00:38:21,440 --> 00:38:23,610
I'm giving you a brighter one.

657
00:38:34,199 --> 00:38:35,800
Don't just stand there.

658
00:38:35,800 --> 00:38:38,528
The light bulb. Give me a hand.

659
00:38:39,239 --> 00:38:41,747
Can't you come down and get it yourself?

660
00:38:50,679 --> 00:38:53,101
Don't look at me like that.

661
00:38:53,101 --> 00:38:54,199
In a month at most,

662
00:38:54,199 --> 00:38:56,039
I'll be leaving here to study abroad.

663
00:38:56,039 --> 00:38:58,760
I'll just treat this like a summer break.

664
00:38:58,760 --> 00:39:01,920
During it, you have the right to be annoyed,
hate me, or dislike me.

665
00:39:01,920 --> 00:39:04,160
But I won't change.

666
00:39:06,240 --> 00:39:08,221
That's the deal between Party A and B.

667
00:39:08,221 --> 00:39:09,680
We endure each other for a month,

668
00:39:09,680 --> 00:39:11,760
and then we're done.

669
00:39:23,880 --> 00:39:25,360
One month at most.

670
00:39:25,360 --> 00:39:26,679
Leave as soon as possible.

671
00:39:26,679 --> 00:39:28,159
Never see you again.

672
00:39:28,159 --> 00:39:30,522
We're on the same page.

673
00:39:32,640 --> 00:39:34,604
Wait.

674
00:39:35,360 --> 00:39:38,719
There are so many sea mosquitoes here.
Do you have any effective repellent?

675
00:39:38,719 --> 00:39:40,935
Some floral water would do.

676
00:39:42,000 --> 00:39:43,360
This is all we have.

677
00:39:43,360 --> 00:39:45,640
Will this work? I don't like the smell.

678
00:39:45,640 --> 00:39:47,800
Don't be picky if you don't want scars.

679
00:39:47,800 --> 00:39:49,822
Take it or leave it.

680
00:39:51,880 --> 00:39:54,092
One more.

681
00:39:55,320 --> 00:39:57,258
Where's the bathroom?

682
00:40:10,480 --> 00:40:11,922
We're here.

683
00:40:12,535 --> 00:40:14,235
Right here.

684
00:40:17,800 --> 00:40:19,679
This is... the bathroom?

685
00:40:19,679 --> 00:40:20,800
Yeah.

686
00:40:20,800 --> 00:40:22,280
A communal bathroom?

687
00:40:22,280 --> 00:40:25,880
I mean... How can neighbors share a bathroom?

688
00:40:25,880 --> 00:40:27,160
You're in Zhazhating.

689
00:40:27,160 --> 00:40:29,240
This is all you got here.

690
00:40:35,679 --> 00:40:38,860
- Right here.
- Why does it smell so bad?

691
00:40:40,520 --> 00:40:43,171
That's rusty!

692
00:40:44,920 --> 00:40:48,054
The floor is so filthy.

693
00:40:49,199 --> 00:40:53,639
The shampoo comes in a bucket, seriously?
How am I supposed to wash here?

694
00:40:53,639 --> 00:40:55,559
There's a water heater and a showerhead.

695
00:40:55,559 --> 00:40:57,480
Why can't you wash?

696
00:40:57,480 --> 00:40:58,920
You're in Zhazhating.

697
00:40:58,920 --> 00:41:00,239
This is all you got here.

698
00:41:00,239 --> 00:41:01,480
What about the door?

699
00:41:01,480 --> 00:41:03,832
How do I lock it?

700
00:41:11,679 --> 00:41:13,222
Well...

701
00:41:18,039 --> 00:41:19,840
There's a hole here.

702
00:41:19,840 --> 00:41:21,840
It's fallen into disrepair. It's broken.

703
00:41:21,840 --> 00:41:23,880
Are you kidding me?

704
00:41:23,880 --> 00:41:25,199
If someone comes by,

705
00:41:25,199 --> 00:41:27,119
they could just squat down and watch me bathe.

706
00:41:27,119 --> 00:41:30,320
It's a hot day.
No one will come here to watch you bathe.

707
00:41:30,320 --> 00:41:33,097
Just pull the curtain closed.

708
00:41:33,097 --> 00:41:36,038
You're in Zhazhating. This is all you got here.

709
00:41:40,360 --> 00:41:42,600
That shampoo...

710
00:41:42,600 --> 00:41:45,400
Is there any other kind?

711
00:41:46,400 --> 00:41:47,497
Yes.

712
00:41:47,497 --> 00:41:49,472
Hey! Wait a second.

713
00:41:50,440 --> 00:41:51,840
Body wash?

714
00:41:51,840 --> 00:41:53,748
Soap.

715
00:41:55,519 --> 00:41:57,992
I'm not used to using soap.

716
00:41:59,119 --> 00:42:00,920
Look.

717
00:42:00,920 --> 00:42:02,320
What are your requirements?

718
00:42:02,320 --> 00:42:04,322
Tell me everything at once.

719
00:42:05,000 --> 00:42:07,320
Shampoo. I want silicone-free shampoo.

720
00:42:07,320 --> 00:42:09,400
And niacinamide facial cleanser.

721
00:42:09,400 --> 00:42:11,676
As for toothpaste, I...

722
00:42:17,199 --> 00:42:18,480
Forget it.

723
00:42:18,480 --> 00:42:20,400
It's only for a month.

724
00:42:20,400 --> 00:42:22,291
I can take it.

725
00:43:16,119 --> 00:43:17,760
Xing Wu, I...

726
00:43:17,760 --> 00:43:19,280
What's wrong?

727
00:43:19,280 --> 00:43:22,119
There's... there's a bug!

728
00:43:22,119 --> 00:43:23,199
A bug?

729
00:43:23,199 --> 00:43:25,647
So many big bugs!

730
00:43:30,139 --> 00:43:31,840
Do you see them?

731
00:43:31,840 --> 00:43:32,920
There are no big bugs.

732
00:43:32,920 --> 00:43:34,280
There are so many!

733
00:43:34,280 --> 00:43:36,085
Is it this one?

734
00:43:36,085 --> 00:43:38,924
Don't... Stay away! Don't come near me!
